Hello and welcome to FROGMAN (c) Matthew Godbolt and Richard Talbot-Watkins. The levels data, graphics and sound files are unprtoected and would probably remain so in the finished game. However, the main code is encrypted using a combination of methods and so is (nearly) unhackable. The disc itself may be freely backed up, but the code itself has the CREDITS file indellibly coded into it, rendering it easy to prove who wrote it. In any finished version, the CREDITS file would be different, and a variety of disc protection methods would be used to stop piracy.MG